The paper proposes a technique for indexing RDF data sets to facilitate efficient SPARQL query evaluation. This falls under the domain of database systems (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of a tree-based indexing structure also suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques for query optimization, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and potentially also falls under the domain of machine learning (cs.LG).
